		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "The granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor ( GM-CSF ) gene has been studied extensively as a model system of transcriptional induction during T-lymphocyte activation . <S>",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "The GM-CSF gene is not expressed in resting peripheral blood T cells",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "but is rapidly induced at the transcriptional level",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "following activation through the cell surface T-cell receptor . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "A highly conserved 19-bp element located immediately 5' of the human GM-CSF TATA box ( bp -34 to -52 ) , herein called purine box 1 ( PB1 ) , has been shown to bind a T-cell nuclear protein complex and to be required for transcriptional induction of the GM-CSF gene",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "following T-cell activation . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "The PB1 sequence motif is highly conserved in both human and murine GM-CSF genes . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "In this report , we demonstrate",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "that the PB1 element alone confers inducibility on a heterologous promoter",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "following transfection into human Jurkat T cells . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "In addition , we identify a major PB1 nuclear protein-binding complex that is not present in resting peripheral blood T cells but is rapidly induced following T-cell activation . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "Sequence analysis revealed",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "that PB1 is composed of adjacent binding sites for Ets and AP-1 transcription factors . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "In vitro mutagenesis experiments demonstrated",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "that both the Ets and AP-1 sites are required for binding of the inducible PB1 nuclear protein complex and for the transcriptional activity of this element and the GM-CSF promoter in activated T cells . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "( ABSTRACT TRUNCATED AT 250 WORDS ) <S>",
